<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>in good nick • in the nick</xh5><p> <i>in good nick</i>—(sl.) in good condition: It’s not a local ale. Last year it turned up in a couple of pubs, sometimes <u>in good nick</u> other times not so good.</p><p><i>in the nick—</i>1. <i>(also: in the nick of time)</i> at a critical moment when smth. urgently requires to be done: Opening our mail we were relieved to discover the catalog had arrived. Just <u>in the nick</u>. 2. <i>(sl.)</i> at a police station or in prison: Everybody <u>in the nick</u> had already been dubbed up for the night.</p> </entry>
